</emphasis>
The female 
<typeStatus box="[451,537,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61">allotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[553,656,464,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,263,1460,1483]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,210,1416]" captionTargetId="figure-284@1.[151,1436,195,1456]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Oaxacanthaxia spp. 1, O. bicolorata, n. sp., male holotype, dorsal aspect; 2, O. bicolorata, n. sp., female allotype, dorsal aspect; 3, same, ventral aspect; 4, holotype, aedeagus, dorsal aspect; 5, O. viridis Bellamy 1991, female paratype, dorsal aspect; 6, O. nigroaenea Nelson &amp; MacRae 1994, female paratype, dorsal aspect; 7, O. vandenberghei Niehuis &amp; Gottwald 2006, female holotype, dorsal aspect; 8, O. aenea Hornburg &amp; Gottwald 2008, male holotype, dorsal aspect. Scale bars = 1.0 mm, the same for Figs. 1–3; no scale for Figs. 7 and 8 from Hornburg &amp; Gottwald (2008): therein Figs. 6 and 8 respectively." pageId="2" pageNumber="61">Figs. 2, 3</figureCitation>
) differs from the 
<typeStatus box="[851,944,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61">holotype</typeStatus>
as follows: length 
<quantity box="[1152,1251,464,487]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.96" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="5.96">5.96 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[1332,1432,464,487]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.86" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="2.86">2.86 mm</quantity>
; head and pronotum essentially the same green to blue-green color, with only a hint of that color reflecting near the anterior margin of elytral disc medially and scutellum; the eyes are slightly smaller, not quite so convex and slightly more widely separated. The 
<typeStatus box="[457,543,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="61">allotype</typeStatus>
appears to be slightly more robust (L/ 
<geoCoordinate box="[956,1050,568,591]" degrees="2.083" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="61" precision="55" value="-2.083">W 2.083</geoCoordinate>
